Comments: I teach a Dual Immersion in Spanish and was looking for Leo Catalog and couldn't find it. I also have not received the Leo Club flyers.  Please don't tell me you discontinued them.

I wanted to set my order date for my parents and am unable to change from the date you have loaded on the site. I have always tried to get our orders in early to enable parents to order and receive books in time for birthdays or holidays...so I wanted our October order to be in the first weekend of the month not the middle. I would appreciate being able to set my own schedule according to the needs of my classroom.  I understand you want to do everything digital and will try your changes. I have always used my rewards to get a book each month for each of my students I am hoping to continue this but fear that parents will not go onto your site to take the time to review what's available.

A little confused with the acronyms to identify the reading levels.  Need better detail as to where I go on  your site to find a more detailed explanation of the reading level acronyms.  GRL:O, GRL:P, GRL:L not sure what that means.
Site freezes and it’s hard to navigate on a phone.  Also, the selection of Spanish books was minimal.
The prices are too HIGH, lower your prices please
I don't like that Scholastic has now chosen my due date for me.  I want to be able to choose when orders are due.

I am sad that you eliminated parents ordering through teachers. I live and teach in a rural district with limited broadband. The paper order option is the only way some of my families are able to participate.
Navigation to eWallet wasn't clear. I had to go to the Questions tab and FAQs - not an intuitive place to find a link to the eWallet.
Once done viewing a book, the back navigation didn't take me back to my last screen search but a prior screen search so I had to start my search over each time I viewed the details of a book.
I was glad that we got orders with the new way to do it. I was concerned that the parents may have problems with it and decided to forgo books.

I am just shocked at the prices of the Scholastic books!  I feel so bad for the families of my students, as this has become unaffordable for so many of them.    I also disagree with not providing the paper order form to the students, this will eliminate at least a fourth of my families, as they do not have internet access.  So disappointed with these changes this year.

Where are all of the promotions and incentives? It seems like the price of books really SHOT up this school  year. You have no books that are in the $1-$2 range at all. Many of us buy class sets of books with our own money and it's very costly to do so now.    Please bring back the old teacher exclusive store. I was saving my Bonus Points for an Apple watch. I just got enough and you removed it from the site.
There should be a teacher's wish list attached to their page so parents can order books for the classroom.
I tried to shop the flyer for 2nd 3rd grade and the site kept showing what seemed like an error code for that level flyer. It said "float: unset" where the 2/3 flyer should have been.
Search is worse than Amazon’s - which is saying a lot. Browse feature is garbage. I’m only placing order so my kid isn’t left out.
I am very disappointed to see that Club Leo is no longer on here and the bilingual and Spanish books are extremely limited.
We love what you bring to our families!
I came to get my Sept. order ready. but was very sad to see that there's not going to be the 10,000 bonus points. That's one of my favorite things that scholastic always does.
Hard to search for books that have won awards. If offered in paperback, should offer in hardcover too and vice versa.

It is difficult to get monthly flyers for my classroom.  I have requested them several times.  The flyers have been sent but just for that month not on a monthly basis.  As a red tier level I feel that they should be sent.  I sent a request for them hopefully they will come quick so I can place an order.  Thank you.
I find your books are very expensive. I can’t order personal books for my own family. It takes forever to find things.
Could not find Theodore Boone books by John Girsham
Way too expensive this year. I won’t be ordering again.

I really can't set my own due dates??  I didn't realize such a big change had been made.  I did notice that the flyers looked a bit different when I sent them home at the end of last week and there wasn't going to be an option for ordering through me which I wasn't too disappointed in but also thought it was a little strange.  Most parents in the past few years had started ordering online but there was a family every once in a while that didn't want to order online or had such a small order that they would just send me the few dollars in cash.  I decided to get on today to check on my account and start my teacher order and noticed that the due date was set and I couldn't change it.  As a teacher that has used Scholastic for many years I was kind of shocked to see such a change.  Also the prices (which I understand with the economy and everything) have just gone up a lot.

I really can't set my own due dates??  I didn't realize such a big change had been made.  I did notice that the flyers looked a bit different when I sent them home at the end of last week and there wasn't going to be an option for ordering through me which I wasn't too disappointed in but also thought it was a little strange.  Most parents in the past few years had started ordering online but there was a family every once in a while that didn't want to order online or had such a small order that they would just send me the few dollars in cash.  I decided to get on today to check on my account and start my teacher order and noticed that the due date was set and I couldn't change it.  As a teacher that has used Scholastic for many years I was kind of shocked to see such a change.  Also the prices (which I understand with the economy and everything) have just gone up a lot.

I do not like that families have to place their orders on Scholastic.com.  I have many families that can't or won't  order because they don't or won't place orders online.  My "teacher order" is actually a student order, but her grandparents don't order things online.  If I didn't place her order, she wouldn't get the books that she desperately needs.  Please go back to allowing paper orders.
It kept flipping back to my account instead of the teacher one.
I would like to receive flyers for 5th graders. Can you please send me some? 3-5 or even middle school?  Thanks for all you do.

I do not like that we cannot set our out due date now.  My due date for October will be late in the month. If families order Halloween books they would get them after Halloween.  I miss the old feature of being able to set our own due dates.
I made an order and I have still not received my order. This order was made over a month ago.
Hard to find books and after look at a book it goes back to the main site….kinda frustrating, but found what I liked.
I kept trying to find out how to get my class on so parents can find me to order. Never can get an answer clicking for how to sign them up.
I just recieved my beginning of the year book order and was going to send it home, but because I was unable to change the parent due date, I will wait until next month.
I am unable to find my child's teach, and because o f that it will not allow me to make the purchase. I could have had the item send to my home.
Second generation with Scholastic Books. Grandchild now reviews book offers through Scholastic. Fantastic selection!

My teacher was not listed in the search bar for my school.  I had to call customer service as there was no place to enter her classroom code.  The representative was able to fix the problem and I completed my order.

I don't like that everything is online and that students cannot order unless they do it online.  Over half my class doesn't have access to the internet so that doesn't help.  I also wish that there were still books that were $1, $2 or $3 dollars making it easier to buy for classes.

I don't like that everything is online and that students cannot order unless they do it online.  Over half my class doesn't have access to the internet so that doesn't help.  I also wish that there were still books that were $1, $2 or $3 dollars making it easier to buy for classes.

I am disappointed with the selections. I feel that the choices are of lesser quality than in previous years. I want to expose my students to high quality literature and some choices seem to be just for playtime.
Had trouble updating my son's teacher. It was slow at loading

I had difficulty entering a cash order from a student, so I just placed it under a "Teacher Order."  I'm guessing that is the way it will be done now.  I'm a proud advocate of "ScholasticBook Clubs," both as a teacher and parent.  I will gladly continue to promote your company.

I really don't like the PRINTABLE LETTERS FOR FAMILIES/Download and Print.  I don't like how Scholastic sets the due date at the top of the letter.  The date should also be editable.  I'd also prefer it if my last name wasn't written in all caps on the signature line.

Wish you guys would bring back Judy Newman dollar books of the month. I have a sponsorship that allows me to get 1 book per student with the $1 books. Very disappointed this year there are no $1 books or $10 for a pack of  10 books of the same ones.

I'll be back, I didn't even know to search for scholastic books.  the site does not GRAB your attention  with correct directions.  missed out on getting $5 free book and could not order the teacher a gift card and pay with PayPal.  will do better next time.

I am very displeased with the way things are set up this year. One, our students here on our campus don't have parents that like to order online so being able to give a paper copy of the order form with cash was a nice option for them. Also, I'm not liking that there isn't a $1 book of the week. I would buy a class copy of each of those books each week. What happened to those? Lastly, what happened to the Dollar Book Store for teachers after reaching $75 in your cart? As someone who usually spends quite a bit of money every year on your online store, I'd like to know what happened to all of these lovely things. Thank you!
I wrote a comment on your feedback page.  I am very disappointed with the prices of your books for the first flyer! I cannot recommend Scholastic Book Clubs until the prices come down!

Scholastic has made it extremely difficult to order books for a decent price. I used to be able to purchase a book for each student for their birthdays, Christmas, Halloween, and end of the year. It's gotten too expensive to do that. I miss the $1 books, true book "deals", and the ease that came with the old way of placing orders. I do not frequent the site very often any more.
I was trying to pull up the flyer and the system kept spinning.
Was trying to transfer an order from the wrong teacher to the correct one and the representative on the live chance only responded once and didn’t answer the follow up questions.
I would appreciate the ability to choose my own due date.
User friendly and extremely well designed
just making sure I had the site set up correctly - do this for our great granddaughter -
I had updated my new teaching assignment to 3rd grade but I only received a book club for middle school, my last lacement.  Please send any that apply to 3rd graders.

I am attempting to enter an order for a student. It appears I can no longer do this? I'm still searching (in case it's there and I just can't locate!) Many families still wish to order through their classroom teacher.
Browsing books isn’t that easy and phone format is hard to navigate
There were no digital flyers for 2nd and 3rd grade!
there should be an app for this

I tried to pay for the books, but a screen popped up saying the web page might be down, or it may have moved to a new web address??????  Sorry!  I love Scholastic Books since forever...and will always recommend people to purchase books from you...but there is a problem with the website!!!!  KEEP READING BOOKS AMERICA!!!!
was not prompted to enter classroom doce, unable to locate school
Heather was very helpful in troubleshooting. Thanks!
Used to be affordable and great selection. Selection options are diminishing and price points are higher than elsewhere.
Just signed up for a homeschool teacher account - very excited! Thank you!

I have been unhappy with the changes I have seen at Scholastic. I do not know that I will continue to regularly use  or recommend Scholastic. The selection of products available in the points store - I have been saving to buy technology for use in my classroom, but you have removed most of the tech. Class sets of books are cheaper to order individually than they are in your "value" packs. Live chat help has been disappointing.
I was checking the bonus points catalog.  I have been saving my points for an iPad.  Once I had enough points, the option is no longer there.
I was unable to change the due date.  I was unable to translate the printable letter into the languages needed for my families.

I have never thought the website has been very user friendly.  I have been placing orders for awhile now and I still struggle.  I also think it is hard to search up books.  I know they are available, but I can't often find them by name.

The error prompt when I tried to order something from the teacher’s wishlist was exceptionally unclear. It took several attempts to figure out that I needed to go to my profile and re-submit (? It was already correct) who his teacher was. Not sure why you can’t just click the button since you’re already on the page for that teacher and ordering books to be shipped to their classroom.  -Figuring out how to get back to the initial screen was unduly difficult. Home button is assumed to lead back to the page that is pulled up when you arrive. Assuming to click on the Scholastic logo isn’t great flow.

I found everything I needed but I couldn’t find my child’s current teacher. They should really update the teachers because some of the teachers listed are not even at the school any more!  That is all.

Very disappointed with the changes in the Book Club this year.  I do not believe I will continue using this program since I cannot change the due date and the flyers hardly have any books in them.  Also used to buy a lot of the $1 books but those are no longer available either.

I do not like not being able to set my own class order date . I logged in today and it says my order only has two day to be placed. I will not send out flyers with less then two days to order and I will not participate if you continue to  dictate  when they are due.

I completed a chat with an agent about hard copy flyers. They informed me that you have stopped printing flyers for the specialty flyers like diverse books and books in spanish. This is removing access to those books from the students who need them the most. Pleaes start printing them again.

I am trying to see why the orders were automatically sent out. I had set my deadline for this Wednesday, but the books have already been delivered.  I don't know if other parents were still planning to order, I don't know if bonus points were accrued, I don't know if I missed opportunities for getting free books for my class. This is different from how it was last year and I don't feel I was provided with the information. Thanks!
I had gotten the book Potato Pants on this site last year and was hoping to get another copy for another teacher on my team, but it is no longer on your site.
I loved that I could get dollar books or group sets of five to get to my kids as gifts. I was dissatisfied with the new system.
Love that you have provided a letter for the parents.
I mailed a check with a payment and it has yet to be cleared on the site.
I'm disappointed to see that book prices have gone up. I hope that this doesn't prevent families from ordering books.
It is confusing how I am now not able to choose my own due date and that the site is doing it for me.

I'm really disappointed to see the $1 and $2 book options not in the flyers and online anymore. We have a low income program and our parents can't afford books. We would provide them with one every month and can no longer afford to at these prices. I can't even describe how frustrating it sad it is to the teachers in our program. Please change it back!!!!!

The price raise on the books is ridiculous.  Teachers already barely make any money.  First you charge us tax for the books, and now you have raised the prices.  How can we get books for our classroom when we can barely afford our classroom supplies which we also have to purchase with our own money.  Scholastic needs to do better.

Please go back to the old system for earning points. The points are too hard to earn and they don't have the value that they used to have.  The points that teachers earned were a major incentive to get students to order books. Now, it has just become a chore with little payoff for the teachers!
Just times out fast and had to keep dog in back in
Site is not as user friendly as it could be. After viewing an individual book, the back button returns to the front page, not my search results.

The navigation on this site is very convoluted.  There's way too many clicks involved to get info.  There should be shortcut buttons on the main page.  Example:  I wanted to see the balance on the accounts for my kids.  I never did figure out how to get to this info.  I used FAQ's, thought I followed the directions but still could not view the info.  I'm very comfortable navigating through websites and I rarely find one that I just don't like but this is one.  If it wasn't for my kids wanting to do the bookfair and me not wanting to send cash....I would not use this website.  This website has the feel of being built, then needing to evolve and instead of updating the entire thing, it was just added on to....several times.  It's very piecemeal and not user friendly.  As for the next question about recommending the book club -- yes, I would recommend Scholastic Book Club but I would not recommend the website.

This book club SUCKS!!! You got rid of the $1.00 and I am furious. I will NEVER use this book club again. I will finish out the year and be done. It would have been nice to know in advance that you are no longer offering $1.00 books. I normally get a book a month for each child. but I cannot afford more than a $1.00. I would not have had people donate to this site. I usually just collect on my own. If I would have collected on my own I could have returned the money. Now I am stuck with this stupid book club. I am so furious.

I would like to see the return of entering student items manually from the teacher page.  Being able to pay in cash tax free made scholastic book orders more accessible to some of my students.    I also would like to print flyers and orders in spanish.  It would assists some families in ordering books for their student.
Please add more pay options like Apple Pay,  goggle pay
I felt like I had to search around a lot. I just want a link to ALL the books that I can then filter.
Only online ordering elevates orders from some students who would order for themselves.
Would like better selection of authors….
good experience and good selection of books
I've heard that there will not be any flyers sent out anymore. Is that correct?
I wanted to submit a September order. It is frustrating that I can not change the date of the orders on the website. This is confusing for families.
It is a little different then what I'm use to
Everything was easy to find for my daughters age group.
It would be nice to have $1 book easier to find.....cost is an issue for most families in our district.
I haven't received flyers yet, and would like some sent please! I was trying to find a spot on the site to have them shipped, but didn't see an option for that.

Using the website to order used to have a slight discount on the book prices - today it didn't seem like that was still the case, or the  buy $25 and get a free book...both of those things helped encourage me at order more in the past.....
QR code takes you to a page that asks age and won’t let you shop. Link on catalog my kid sent home took me somewhere weird too. Had to find this manually.
Quite useful. Not sure about all the reading level abbreviations, but that is probably my own lack of knowledge.
Couldn’t figure out exactly which 6 books came in the pigeon pack. I had to use outside resources and assume they’re correct.
It would be helpful for teachers to be able to adjust our class due date.  It is ridiculous that it is determined by Scholastic.

I am not receiving book catalogs and I didn't get them last year either.  Another teacher would let me have an extra catalog each month so I could pass them out to my students.  (Firefly or whichever early childhood receives).    PLEASE start sending catalogs to me every month! thank you.  My name and address are the same as its been for years.  Nothing has changed.  Thank you
But only problem was in the finding the school area…

I am at a school site where many parents do not actively use technology or have access to computers. I tried to place an order for my students, but was unable to log them in under "Family Orders" as this did not allow me to. I had to place my classroom book order under "Teacher Orders". I do not like the change in the way families have to order as it does not suit all demographics nor does it allow for equal access to books simply because of technology. This made logging which books each student ordered, very difficult because there was no place for me to add the child's name. Please go back to the "old" system, as this is what parents and teachers are accustom to when placing an order.

I was searching for Club Leo since I am a bilingual teacher and 100% of my students are native Spanish speakers. They predominantly order Spanish books since they are developing their native language. Will Club Leo be back in the future? Why was Club Leo taken out?

1.  I couldn't find where to enter the order for students.  In the past, you entered the student's name.    2.  I have to pay $6.25 in taxes.  My parents just sent the money stated on the books order for each book.  Now, I have to pay taxes when I give my students a book order.      3.  Now, I have to pay to mail in the checks/cash from my families.  There was no envelop provided the the Scholastic Packet.    I am not impressed with these changes.  As an educator, I pay for enough out of my pocket.     I have ordered books with Scholastic for 34 years.  (The  last years with COVID have been off!)
I am so happy to be able to get books for my nephew! I loved getting them when I was in school. The nostalgia is heartwarming.
I can't find how to add my $10 free books.  I also couldn't find the teacher bonus catalog.  This was confusing and I have been using Scholastic for years.

I am not sure about changes. The preassigned date is new to me and it seems like the flyers are getting to me later than usual..... I just received  the Back to school and have not yet received the Fall Order Form and apparently my order is due October 11. I would like to send out this week.

Why can I not change my class order anymore???  This use to be so user friendly and I could send a class order when I felt it was a good time for my class.  Now I'm being told when my families can place an order!  This isn't ok!!!  I've spent thousands of dollars on this site and do not like what is happening......

I want the parents to still be able to use the class code, as well as search by teacher.  Both should be options.  I think some of my parents might not know our zip code off hand, but they will know the class code. I don't see a place to enter the class code any more.
I cannot enter my full card number. I can only add the 1st 13 numbers.

Unfortunately, Scholastic submitted a parent order automatically and didn't wait for me to submit the order. Because it was the first order of the year I allowed a few weeks. This changed the number of bonus points I received for my order.
It was difficult to figure out how to let my parents know my code. The new flyer send them to the website but how I can make sure they buy books on my name and code?
Cannot see covers for free book selection
I do not think students will purchase as n  Many books without the traditional format of bringing payments to school
Was not able to place pre orders
When it asked for my birthday, it wasn’t obvious that it wanted my birthday and not my child’s.
I was looking for the book of the week
Would have given a 5 because the site was easy to use but it was not very clear in the pamphlet that you had to log in to place an order
The prices of books has really gone up.

I was surprised to receive an email from Scholastic. It states that there is a family order placed in my name.  I had not advertised that I would take orders online. It isn’t a problem, and I will make sure it is accepted.
Couldn’t find the where to enter the class code.
I find your new site confusing. I miss the baby toddler section.

I did not experience any problems with the site but I find that families are a bit reluctant to order without having the paper flyer to look through.  I think that our families that are readers/ educated will take the time to browse the site but many others will not.  I do not mind collecting and sending in the order.  I think that this is definitely an equity issue.  I am sad that many kids will not be ordering books.  I also think that the prices have risen drastically and parents may just choose to order off of Amazon or similar sites. I used to order class sets of the dollar books and put those in the hands of many students.

I am not pleased with the new design and options for scholastic book clubs. There is no option for a teacher to enter an order for a student whose parents don't want to create an account. My teacher order is charged tax even though the school is tax-exempt. Can a check even be mailed for an order?

I am not pleased with the new design and options for scholastic book clubs. There is no option for a teacher to enter an order for a student whose parents don't want to create an account. My teacher order is charged tax even though the school is tax-exempt. Can a check even be mailed for an order?

I am disappointed with the selections. I feel that the choices are of lesser quality than in previous years. I want to expose my students to high quality literature and some choices seem to be just for playtime.
Bring back $1 books for all children especially those who can’t spend $25+ on books!

I know everything has gone up everywhere, but I'm trying to buy my students a new book every month and it is hard to afford 21 books. I've had to give them a different book from the rest of the class.
searched and went back looking for the ship to home option.  Disappointed that the option is no longer there at check out
I couldn't find the flip charts.

Sometimes search function does not work. I have searched for a product (correct spelligng etc) and the item is not available, then I come across it while browsing other items. Also, would love to have individual books from complete series (you don't seem to have the 2nd Sweet Valley Twins book). Some seriers only seem to be partially available.

I am VERY disappointed in the bonus catalog. I have been saving my points to buy some gift cards and you have taken EVERYTHING that is good off teacher's store.  I think an email needed to be sent BEFORE you did this so us teachers that have been saving our points could have spent them. I have been with you for 30 years.  I have heard other teachers are not very happy about this decision as well. I really hope you make it right for us LOYAL customers that have been with you for YEARS.
I dislike the fact that you can no longer edit the due date for the orders.

Please sell books individually and not just as "bundles."  Too many books come only as "bundles."  If there's a specific book I want, I'd like to purchase it by itself.  It's expensive to have to buy a $20+ bundle.  I end up just getting it from the library instead, because $20 is too expensive to have to buy a bunch of books I don't want, just to get the book I do want.  Please include "Melissa" by Alex Gino for ordering.

There is nowhere to use the "Class Code" I was provided by my child's teacher. Your FAQ does not mention the "Class Code", only how to register *without* it. Your registration form does not ask for the "Class Code". I tried searching by ZIP code and found my school, but my child's teacher does not show in the search results.     Also, the very first page of the website asks for a birthdate. I interpreted this to mean the website wanted my child's birthday but the website does not continue past the initial page if I use my child's birthday and it gives absolutely no feedback to the user as to what the problem is. (I did eventually figure out that it wanted MY birthday, but what use is my birthday to your site? Isn't it more useful to know the age of my child?)    I was excited to place an order from Scholastic out of nostalgia for my own book-ordering experiences as a kid but your site is a mess that has done little to encourage me to continue any further.
The number of pop-ups- or things that come down- is annoying!

Was not able to chose shipment to my address instead it will be shipped to my daughter’s teacher. This will create confusion for her teacher as she lives in two separate households and past orders went home with her to the other household creating more confusion for the other parent who poorly communicates with me. I would much rather have the option to pay the shipping cost myself so the order can come directly to me.

I noticed you streamlined the site but it isn't as user friendly as years previous. I was looking for my class order information (to revise due date) and it wasn't easy to locate. I also wish you had an easier way to add other catalogs for families to look at. (I shared the link of the catalogs, which I hope works because it was from the teacher login.)  Your prices are too high, less selection. (There are huge differences between grade levels that you don't seem to recognize.). Second graders reading levels and content are not the same as third graders. I think you (and teachers) will lose purchases because parents will feel selection is not appropriate/varied/advanced enough.
It is very difficult to know which part of the site you are in and the serach function does not seem to be comprehensive across  different areas (flyers vs. general).
As an Educator and Parent I love Scholastic Book Club.
Information or a chart on reading level would be helpful.
I feel as though the same books keep appearing and it is difficult to suggest new book titles to parents.
I like getting the paper copies of book orders rather than sending the information via email to parents. I don't have anyone interested in books when it's digital.
The search parameters are very difficult. Looking for Spanish language books and it is very difficult to find and there is no section for books in Spanish.
Would like more categories to select. Often the ‘More like this’ brought up books not related at all
Promo code, it’s annoying having to go back and find it. Honestly hate scholastic … they have none of the good stuff they used too when I was a kid. Get some classics

I do not like the updated mandatory due dates for students and teachers.  My first order did not include nearly as many orders as in the past to get the first of the year bonus points because I was not able to reach parents to remind them before the parent order was submitted.
page does not fit my screen which requires lots of scrolling up and down which is difficult for excited impatient kids

I miss the ability to order books by students' names.  I have students who give me cash for books.  Now I have to put them under my teacher order.  Not everyone orders books online! Out of my order today-3 out of 5 orders were student paper orders with cash.
I wish that I could order books that are in a series, INDIVIDUALLY.  I would like to order several copies of Front Desk - but I don't need several copies of the entire set.

The site is very confusing. I found my kids' book fair but I cannot find how to add to the ewallet. I've just purchased 2 different ecards for each of my kids becasue its the only way i could find to add any $ to their accounts.  They haven't come through my email yet so hopefully when they do I can add them easily. I'm not hopeful, though.  It should be obvious where to "add $ to your ewallet"  and how to send the info out to family members to add $ as well. I need to send their info their dad but don't see anywhere how to do that.
My kids and I love ordering new books through the online Scholastic site. Thank you!

Don't love the new preset dates that I am not able to adjust.  If there is a lot going on at my school, I like to try and move the dates to better times so I'm not bombarding parents with too much to do at once.  I work at a low-income and highly ELL school and many families used to send me in paper orders. Not in love with online purchases only now. Usually my first order of the year is HUGE and I had 1 this year.
I’ve been an avid reader since a young child thanks to you!!
it took me to the survey first so i don't believe my order has been placed yet
Having family orders exclusively online may exclude some of my families, such as my non-English speakers and families without access to technology, from ordering books.
10% off code offered at checkout did not work. Code: READMORE

Dear Scholastic,  I do not know how you can justify wrapping every single book club catalog in plastic. What an absurd waste. I just received 7 separate, identical catalogs each in its own plastic wrap that is completely unnecessary. To make it even worse, many of them were to generic "teacher of grades 4 and 5". It's one thing if I can actually distribute them to a teacher, but those that are vague are an even more absurd waste of resources. Please, please, please stop.   We strive to be a sustainable school. Putting this much unnecessary plastic in the trash and paper in the recycle bin is in direct conflict with our goals. It makes me want to cease all orders with your company. Please let me know what information you need so that we stop receiving generic teacher mailings. And none of them needs to be encased in plastic!  Thank you.

I am EXTREMELY disappoint in the condition the books have arrived this last year. With the price of books, I want to receive my books the way they are expected--in new condition. Every time I reach out to customer service, the hassle is so extensive that it is not worth ordering any longer. I will spend my points and will NO LONGER make any Scholastic orders. I refuse to keep giving parents books in worse condition than found at a yard sale. I will order from other book retailers. It has been this way since 2020, post Covid.
